This paper discusses the extraction of text from web pages, which is a common task in information retrieval (cs.IR) and web search (cs.WEB). The paper also mentions issues with parsing HTML, which is a topic in natural language processing (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper discusses issues with acquiring content from web archives, which could fall under the category of digital libraries (cs.DL) or computer security (cs.CR) if the focus is on preserving and securing archived content.
